I just realized that my code doesn't call continue properly on the outer loop once we know it's qualifier (so we needn't process it any further). And so does yours. We should take that into account, so in fact it should look something like this:
            Collection<AnnotationInstance> qualifierCollection = beanDeployment.getQualifierExtractor(annotation.name()).apply(annotation);
            for (AnnotationInstance qualifierAnnotation : qualifierCollection) {
                // Qualifiers
                qualifiers.add(qualifierAnnotation);
            }
            if (!qualifierCollection.isEmpty()) {
                // we needn't process it further, the annotation was a qualifier (or multiple repeating ones)
                continue;
            }

